TextEquiv.Unicode: Propter fidem quam dederat hosti. Cic. [Cic. also says, for to keep s
promise, fidem servo, exsolvo, præsto, in fide sto; for to break a promi,
fidem violo, fallo, frango, in fide non sto.]—A man who had made him s
solemn promise to be wholly devoted to him. Qui se illius fore proprium
fide confirmarat. Nep.—Wise old men are pleased with young men of
promise. Adolescentibus bonâ indole præditis sapientes senes delectantu.
Cic.—A young man of the greatest promise, both in genius and dispo-
tion. Adolescens sumâ spe et animi, et ingenii præditus. Cic.—A
daughter of great promise. Egregiæ spei filia. Tac.
